CSP-105 / Primitive 93
MOGRI â€“ FULL CANONICAL FORM LIST
STATUS: AUTHORITATIVE
NOTE: This list enumerates ALL permitted mogri forms.
      Forms are grouped by role and marked by pack of origin.

============================================================
CORE GRAMMAR PACK (REQUIRED)
============================================================

mogri
  noun (singular)
  The primitive phenomenon of epistemic distortion caused by
  over-structuring, over-explanation, or misaligned narration.

mogris
  noun (plural)
  Multiple instances of mogri.

mogrify
  verb
  To induce or undergo mogri.

mogrifies
  verb (present, 3rd person singular)

mogrifying
  verb (present participle)
  Active degradation of clarity through added explanation.

mogrified
  verb / adjective (past participle)
  A stabilised state in which meaning has been distorted.

mogric
  adjective
  Susceptible to mogri; at risk of epistemic degradation.

mogrificant
  adjective
  Actively inducing mogri.

============================================================
EXTENDED GRAMMAR PACK 01 (EXPRESSIVE / MARKED)
============================================================

mogrific
  adjective (expressive)

mogrificent
  adjective (expressive)

mogrificatory
  adjective (expressive)

mogrificationistic
  adjective (expressive)

mogrificationisticant
  adjective (expressive)

mogritiv
  adjective (expressive)

mogritant
  adjective (expressive)

------------------------------------------------------------
Prefixed expressive adjectives (dis-)
------------------------------------------------------------

dismogric
dismogrious
dismogriantic
dismogricious
dismogrificant

------------------------------------------------------------
Prefixed expressive adjectives (contra-)
------------------------------------------------------------

contramogric
contramogrious
contramogriantic
contramogricious
contramogrificant

NOTE:
All Pack 01 forms are permitted only when explicitly marked
as expressive, scholastic, or illustrative.
They are not required for correct usage.

============================================================
GRAMMAR PACK 02 (CLOSURE & BOUNDARY PROTECTION)
============================================================

mogring
  gerund / activity noun
  Low-stakes, ambient engagement without escalation
  or transformation.

mogried
  state adjective / past-participle analogue
  Natural completion of mogring without boredom or residue.

============================================================
SUMMARY
============================================================

Canonical floor (required for functionality):
- 9 forms (core grammar + Pack 02)

Total canonical forms (all packs combined):
- 24 forms

No additional mogri forms are valid unless added
via formal revision of CSP-105.

END OF CANONICAL LIST
